
// The jsc (JavaScript Compiler) configuration is a core part of SWC that controls
// how TypeScript/JavaScript code is parsed and transformed. The parser.syntax option
// tells SWC to treat input files as TypeScript, enabling TypeScript-specific features
// like type annotations, interfaces, and generics. The target option specifies the
// ECMAScript version to compile down to - es2022 provides modern JavaScript features
// while maintaining broad compatibility.